63.4	Virtue_ethics	Virtue ethics	Virtue ethics describes the character of a moral agent as a driving force for ethical behavior, rather than rules , consequentialism (which derives rightness or wrongness from the outcome of the act itself rather than character), or social context (pragmatic ethics).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Aristoteles_Louvre.jpg/100px-Aristoteles_Louvre.jpg
